    "created_at": "2015-09-22T20:10:55Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-22T20:10:55Z",
    "body": "Right now I've been working around this with this hack. On systems with minimal to no window chrome it works well enough for my application.\n\n``` javascript\nvar minWidth = 500;\nvar minHeight = 400;\nvar ratio = 1;\nif (window.outerWidth < window.innerWidth) {\n  ratio = window.outerWidth / window.innerWidth;\n}\nrequire('remote').getCurrentWindow().setMinimumSize(Math.round(ratio * minWidth), Math.round(ratio * minHeight));\n```\n\nI've tried clamping it to nearest 0.25 values to get around the extra pixels the window chrome adds but depending on your monitor the exact value of this ratio may not be a perfectly round decimal.\n"
  },
